EASY Buck can continue his progress and claim some notable scalps by taking the
Tripleprint Gold Cup at Cheltenham this afternoon.
The winner of six of his 12 races over the larger obstacles, he once beat
Baydon Star out of sight as a novice and seems to improve with each run.
He was going well when an unlucky faller here at the Festival in March.
After having joined the Nigel Twiston-Davies' stable during the summer, Easy
Buck showed his well-being with a comfortable win at Newbury.
Still at the right end of the handicap and with the admirable Chris Maude on
board, he has every chance of landing this big prize.
Couldnt Be Better was an impressive winner of the Hennessy but may find himself
tapped for speed and Big Matt and Gnome's Tycoon can fill the places.
Mysilv looks set to enjoy her fifth win over today's course and distance in the
Bula Hurdle.
It was asking a lot for her to make all in last season's Champion Hurdle and
she was clearly tired at the last but had the guts to hold on to fifth place,
clear of Atours and Mole Board.
Atours is expected to be more of a force here but may simply lack the class of
Charlie Egerton's mare.
Putty Road was about the best novice hurdler around last year, and it was hard
to believe that he could be beaten at odds-on in a four-horse race on his
reappearance.
That result, however, seemed a lot less surprising after the winner, Chief's
Song, had gone on to land last week's William Hill Hurdle against strong
opposition.
Putty Road can reassert his top-class status at the expense of Killone Abott in
the Lonesome Glory Hurdle.
It is not much of a tip to note that One Man only has to stand up to win the
feature race at Haydock. Better odds are on offer at Doncaster, where Cogent
has an excellent chance of returning to the winner's enclosure.
This doughty stayer should be suited by conditions underfoot and has the
measure of Scotton Banks.
q THE chances of racing at Lingfield this afternoon disappeared under a frozen,
white blanket yesterday.
A course spokesman said: ``There is still snow on the course and although there
was a slight thaw in the morning, the temperature has again dropped. ``Any snow
that is left will therefore still be there tomorrow.''
</TEXT>
