<HEADLINE>Millie on a mission</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>nigel duncan</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974979116</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ICE HOCKEY
LES Millie has a quick chance of revenge over his former team-mates tonight
when he plays for Fife Flyers against newly-crowned Benson and Hedges Cup
winners Sheffield Steelers at Kirkcaldy.
The Yorkshiremen, currently third in the premier division, hammered
third-bottom Flyers on their own rink 13-3 two weeks ago with Millie failing to
make the scoresheet.
Mark Morrison, the Kirkcaldy club's player-coach, said: ``Les has fitted in
well since joining us from Sheffield and is determined to do well against his
old club. That heavy defeat hurt us and we need points to lift ourselves up the
table. A result against the strongest club in the league would give everyone a
lift.''
Meanwhile, promotion-pushing Dumfries Vikings could have new signing Luc Chabot
in their line-up at home to Telford tonight, and Paisley Pirates are anxious to
halt a run of five straight defeats at Chelmsford tonight.
NIGEL DUNCAN
</TEXT>
