<HEADLINE>Street celebrates its 35th birthday and a wedding</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974979133</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE cast of television soap Coronation Street attended a dinner last night to
celebrate its 35th birthday.
The Manchester Town Hall bash went on as millions of viewers tuned in to watch
barmaid Raquel - actress Sarah Lancashire - marry Curly Watts, actor Kevin
Kennedy.
The hour-long episode was filmed amid strict secrecy and was expected to
attract more than 20 million viewers.
Three different endings to storyline involving dizzy Raquel, her ex-lover Des
Barnes and Curly were filmed before programme chiefs made a late decision on
which to screen.
Arriving at the official party, Miss Lancashire wore a black evening dress with
drop neckline and wore a ruby necklace as she smiled and waved on the town hall
steps.
She arrived arm-in-arm with the show's creator Tony Warren and actresses
Sherrie Hewson, shopkeeper Maureen Holdsworth, and Amanda Barrie, cafe owner
Alma Baldwin.
Last night's episode finally saw womanising Des sweet-talk Raquel into his flat
and into bed after his married girlfriend Liz McDonald ends their brief fling.
Later, in a fit of disillusionment in the cold light of day Raquel decided to
marry long-time suitor, Curly Watts. After the registry office wedding viewers
were still left wondering about the TV couple's future happiness.
Raquel was shown sobbing in the ladies' toilet minutes before the ceremony,
then going through her marriage vows with an anguished look - and a drawn-out
pause before she uttered the words `` . . .  my lawful, wedded husband.''
</TEXT>
