<TEXT>
THE Scottish Office Minister for Industry George Kynoch yesterday praised the
work of two centres at Livingston, West Lothian, which provide many of the
skilled technicians required for the expanding electronics industry in
Scotland.
He toured the Scottish Mechatronics Centre and Lothian Electronic Training
Services (Lets) during a visit arranged by Lothian and Edinburgh Enterprise Ltd
(LEEL).
