<HEADLINE>Second Russian killed in polls</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974979177</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A CANDIDATE in this month's Russian elections has been shot dead on his
doorstep in the second murder of the campaign.
Mikhail Lezhnev, 48, owner of a successful poultry farm, was found dead outside
his home near Chelyabinsk in the Ural mountains overnight. He had been shot in
the head.
His death, less than two weeks after MP Sergei Markidonov was killed on the
campaign trail in Siberia, heightened concern that violence could mar the
election.
Lezhnev was a candidate for Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin's centre-right
Our Home is Russia movement, which said the killing was politically-motivated.
He had been married with grown-up children.
Police spokesman Boris Mityurev said Lezhnev had been leading in opinion polls
in his constituency but that it was not clear if his death was linked with
business or politics.
``We do not know who killed him. No-one saw the killing,'' he said. However
local sources said Lezhnev was probably shot by a professional killer as
another businessman survived a similar attempt on his life yesterday.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
