<TEXT>
YOU'VE warmed to the tales of everyday folk in a quaint Yorkshire village.
You've even been tempted to buy the CD of tunes and croons which accompany them.
Now, it's time to try out the recipes. The Heartbeat Country Cookbook is a
selection of traditional Yorkshire favourites by Tom Bridge. Scarborough
Seafood Kebabs washed down with a flagon of Father O' Malleys ginger beer
anyone? Well, perhaps not, but there are more than 150 delicious recipes to
warm the coldest northern winter. Good Crimbo pressie for fans of the series
too. (Cassell #9.99).
</TEXT>
