n IF you're planning a fly/drive holiday in America, check the car insurance
policy before you leave. Most US rental companies provide only limited cover
and it is vital you read the whole insurance policy. One company worth using to
get over problems is Inter Assurance (01252 717766). They claim their new
top-up policy at #50 for eight days cover will take care of any situation you
are likely to encounter, while costing no more than the policies you are
generally offered by car rental companies which provide only a quarter of the
pay-outs.
n AVRO have flights to Alicante on December 23 for #174, Malaga on December 21
for #175 and Tenerife on December 19 for #254. Call 0141 303 0303.
n ACCORDING to the Central Statistical Office's latest Travel Trends, France
and Spain are still the top destinations for Brits, accounting for more than
40% of all holidays in 1994. More than eight million visits to Spain were made
last year, compared to only 700,000 visits made by Spanish nationals to the UK.
France accounted for nine million visits by Britons.
Turkey has risen most dramatically as a mainstream destination. 721,000
holidayed there in 1994, compared to 329,000 in 1992.
Tourists from the UK spend an average #363 abroad, #100 less than our inbound
tourists. The good news for our inbound tourism industry is that a record 21
million trips were made last year, more than double the number 20 years ago.
n THOMSON Holidays and Airtours will both use Sandford Airport in Florida next
year for its packages to Orlando. No more will you fly to Orlando, and the
substitute airport is 40 minutes further away from the Mickey Mouse resort.
Operators say the extra driving time will be made up for by the faster
processing time it takes to get through Sandford Airport, which is,
coincidentally, a cheaper option for them to use.
n SCOTLAND'S newest ski area, Nevis Range, is expecting to attract an
additional 12,000 skiers this winter following installation of two new lifts
and more than doubling the size of its skiable terrain. Located seven miles
from Fort William, the area of Back Coire Dubh is now within the resort - good
news as it gets some of the first snowfalls of the season. Catering facilities
have also been expanded with the opening of the snack hut at the Rob Roy tow.
Nevis range will be the location of the British Schools Race on March 18 and
the Ski Centre Club Championship on March 31. On the other side of the country,
Aviemore expects to be given planning permission for its funicular any day now.
The lift will be operational by winter 96/97.
n BETWEEN January 2 and February 29 Highlife London &amp; UK Breaks is deducting #5
a person from bookings on the four star Johnstounburn House near Edinburgh.
Prices start at #45 for B&amp;B in this beautiful historic mansion.
n CRYSTAL Holidays has added a new cottage to its autumn/spring Premier Britain
programme which overlooks the 18th green of St Andrews golf course. The lodge
sleeps up to six and costs from #500 a night.
n SUPERBREAK is offering a three-night Christmas break starting December 23 in
the four star Marine Highland Hotel in Troon for #295 full board. This includes
a whisky tasting and visit to Ayr Races on Boxing Day. Travel agents can still
book you.
n A LAST minute Christmas getaway to Madeira is available from Cadogan
Holidays. The 12-night break leaves on December 22 and costs #499 per person.
Flights are from Gatwick and accommodation on a B&amp;B basis is in a four star
hotel. Half board is available for an extra #15 a day. Call 01703 332661.
n FRED Olsen Travel has launched its 1996 brochure covering holidays on the
Coastal Express for the period January to October. For the first time hotel
stays in Norway are tied in with cruises, with Aberdeen departures to Bergen.
Prices start at #1060 for an eight-night holiday. Travel agents have brochures
or call 01473 292222.
n YOU don't have to join the army to drive a military vehicle. Anglian Activity
Breaks is offering the chance to drive a 55-ton Chieftain tank and a whole
range of other military vehicles. Typical prices are #85 per person for any two
drives and #56 for a package including a gun carrier, Honda Pilot race, 4X4
off-road drive, go-kart and fun reverse-steer vehicle. With more than 100
pursuits in their brochure if you're looking for a wacky weekend, call 01508
495008 for a brochure.
n COTSWOLD Cycling Company (01242 250642) has put together pre-ski cycling and
exercise weekends to get those sluggish muscles back in shape before hitting
the pistes. The muscle groups used in skiing are apparently the same as those
used in cycling, so what better way to get fit. The Cheltenham-based weekends
include exercise sessions with a qualified fitness instructor and guided cycle
rides over the Cotswold terrain. Ski-based videos will also be shown. The cost
is from #78 per person (#51 with own bike). Dinner is #15 extra and the
exercise and cycling can also be taken without the accommodation for #57 per
person. Weekends are taking place January 6/7, January 20/21 and February 3/4.
</TEXT>
