<HEADLINE>Scent of a woman</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ANVAR KHAN</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Features</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>weekend extra</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974979320</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
n ``Put a tummy on her, real women have stomachs,'' ordered French designer,
Jean Paul Gaultier, when he came face to face with the prototype for his
bottled fragrance.
The body-bottle is clothed in a detachable copper-coloured corset, and what was
originally underneath was too skinny. Gaultier is chubby and broad, he's a man
who loves his food, and he wants everyone else to enjoy theirs too. He decided,
therefore, that Gaultier, the 75ml spray, should smell edible. The fragrance
consists of vanilla and ginger, and suggests the warmth of a baker's and the
sweetness of hot icing sugar.
Interestingly, the high-camp bottled scent does not appeal to young women but
to more mature types. Maybe then you develop the necessary sense of fun to wear
it. Jean Paul Gaultier has an additional bath range including pebble grey soap
which has a hologram of woman inside when you hold it up to the light.
Jean Paul Gaultier 75ml Eau de Toilette Refillable Natural Spray #46.50; Jean
Paul Gaultier 75ml Eau de Toilette Refill #38.00.
n While we're on perfume, a surefire winner this Christmas is Kashaya de Kenzo
by the Japanese designer. Although he is an oriental, he is fascinated with
India and devised this fragrance as a testament to love, after seeing the Taj
Mahal. The 25ml bottle of Eau de Parfum Spray is #26 and smells like a hundred.
A mixture of apricot and blue rose, lotus flowers and Cattleya orchids, it is
lighter than Guerlain's Shalimar, but just as spicy. The bath range starts at
#10.50.
n Hermes, the scarf house, have launched a perfume named after their Paris shop
- ``24, Faubourg'' - a woody, dusty, religious scent with jasmine, ylang-ylang
and vanilla, which smells as if you've just opened a hundred-year-old trunk in
which silk scarves have lain alongside gold, frankincense and myrrh. It is for
strong, mature women, or for girls who want to go for it in the evenings. It's
classy and it's expensive. Parfum 15ml is #88, Parfum 30ml #135, but 50ml Eau
de Toilette Sprays start at #36.50.
</TEXT>
